node.text:
The Marieta Islands are a group of small uninhabited islands a few miles off the coast of Mexico 😍 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @globefever 

One of the popular tourist destination in the Islands is "love beach", also called the "hidden beach". It’s entirely hidden, and can only be reached by swimming through a short, narrow tunnel. While the beach itself is natural, the sinkhole is reportedly man-made. The Mexican government started using the islands as target practice prior to the First World War. These controlled bombings have formed numerous sinkholes. So, most likely a natural cave roof is collapsed due to bombings.

📽 @postandfly
📍Marieta islands, Mexico
🎶 Gustavo Bravetti - Babel

node.text:
Rainbow Island, Iran 🇮🇷 We can post your photos in our account, follow the link in our bio: @globefever and we will select your pictures 

The soil composing Hormuz Island in #Iran is highly concentrated with Iron Oxide. This concentration leads to red coloration, which is washed up in the waves.
Have you ever seen anything like this?

📽 @elhamgholami
📍 Hormuz, Iran

node.text:
Wild ride 🐎 We can post your photos in our account, follow the link in our bio: @globefever and we will select your pictures 

Bareback riding is a form of horseback riding without a saddle. It requires skill, balance, and coordination, as the rider does not have any equipment to compensate for errors of balance or skill.

Proponents of bareback riding argue that riding in this fashion is natural, allows considerable communication with the horse, and improves a rider's balance. The drawbacks include a higher risk of injury due to an increased risk of falling off the horse, the potential to develop poor riding form, and the possibility of considerable discomfort to both horse and rider due to the absence of a supporting tree and any padding between the rider's seat bones and the horse's spine. Over time, it is more fatiguing to both horse and rider to ride bareback.

📽 @kerrikasem
🎶 Sting - Desert Rose (feat. Cheb Mami)
📍 Essaouira, Morocco

Ticino is the southernmost canton of Switzerland. 🇨🇭 Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting globefever.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @globefever 

It's an Italian-speaking region in southern Switzerland with palm-lined lakes and sharp Alpine peaks. Its architecture, cuisine and culture is closely related to that of neighboring Italy. Bellinzona, the capital of Ticino, is home to medieval castles. Lugano, a town on glacial Lake Lugano, is known for its waterfront promenade and Piazza della Riforma, a square lined with neoclassical buildings.

📷 @giuliogroebert
📍Ticino, Switzerland

node.text:
Diving deep into a new adventure with @irisschmidbauer 🌊😨 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @globefever 

Would you be brave enough to jump from a 27m cliff (88ft)?

Disclaimer: Iris is a professional cliff diver, do not attempt this by yourself.

📽 @irisschmidbauer
📍 Sao Miguel, Azores, Portugal
🎶 Otnicka - Where Are You
